column1: Intercensal Estimates of the Resident Population of States and Counties
Source: U.S. Bureau of the Census
Population Estimates and Population Distribution Branches

Method: The intercensal formula for the 1980s is described in Current Population Reports, Series P25-1106.  The formula was applied to both state and county estimates.  The intercensal estimates are based on census counts which include the latest corrections available at the time of production. The methodology for the 1980s postcensal estimates is described in P26-88A, and in several technical papers emanating from the Population Estimates Branch.  For a copy of these reports call (301) 457-2422, for technical papers and questions call (301) 457-2380.
Note: See diskette PE-1 for 1980s counties components of change.
C.A.= Census Area   Bor.= Borough  Par.= Parish
